# ⚙️ Team Rules

## 1. Long execution blocks > meetings

The schedule maximizes uninterrupted modeling time.

---

## 2. Every day ends with 3 questions

1. What improved?
2. What do we kill?
3. What is tomorrow’s highest-impact task?

---

## 3. Every sync must include
- current best CV
- current best model
- biggest blocker/risk

---

## 4. Kill weak ideas early

Fast iteration beats over-engineering.

---

# ✅ Why This Structure Works

- fewer interruptions
- more deep-work time
- cleaner accountability
- faster experimentation cycles
- lower coordination overhead

For a short ML sprint, this is usually the optimal cadence.
